-- Chilean Stocks: Cap, E-CL and Soc. Quimica & Minera Advance
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2011-12-19T21:19:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/chilean-stocks-cap-e-cl-and-soc-quimica-minera-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index closed little changed at 4,140.81. The  MSCI
Chile (MXCL)  index retreated 0.6 percent to 2,231.57.  CAP SA (CAP)   rose 0.7 percent to 18,972 pesos. Chile’s
largest iron ore miner and steel producer said the cost of
developing its Cerro Negro Norte project had increased to $800
million, according to a statement posted today on its website.  E-CL SA (ECL)   advanced 0.9 percent to 1,347.5 pesos.
Northern Chile’s largest power generator may be included in the
benchmark Ipsa index in 2012, according to a simulation
published Dec. 16 on the website of the Santiago exchange.  Soc. Quimica & Minera de Chile SA  (SQM/B CC) gained 2.4
percent, the most in eight weeks, to 27,228 pesos.  Chile ’s
largest fertilizer producer said in a statement Dec. 16 that it
sold mining assets in northern Chile to Sierra Gorda SCM for
$37.8 million, plus an annual royalty payment of $2 million
beginning in 2022. The move will add $30 million to fourth-
quarter earnings, the company said.  The company was also initiated at “overweight” at Itau
Unibanco Holding SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
